  <Name>k__BackingField: Jonah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: jon
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jonah\u2019s Disobedience"
      title: "Jonah\u2019s Disobedience"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the word of the Lord came to Jonah the son of Amittai, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to Nineveh, that great city, and proclaim [judgment] against
        it, for their wickedness has come up before Me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But Jonah ran away to Tarshish to escape from the presence of the
        Lord [and his duty as His prophet]. He went down to Joppa and found a ship
        going to Tarshish [the most remote of the Phoenician trading cities]. So
        he paid the fare and went down into the ship to go with them to Tarshish
        away from the presence of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But the Lord hurled a great wind toward the sea, and there was a
        violent tempest on the sea so that the ship was about to break up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the sailors were afraid, and each man cried out to his god;
        and to lighten the ship [and diminish the danger] they threw the ship\u2019s
        cargo into the sea. But Jonah had gone below into the hold of the ship and
        had lain down and was sound asleep. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the captain came up to him and said, \u201CHow can you stay asleep?
        Get up! Call on your god! Perhaps your god will give a thought to us so that
        we will not perish.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they said to another, \u201CCome, let us cast lots, so we may
        learn who is to blame for this disaster.\u201D So they cast lots and the
        lot fell on Jonah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CNow tell us! Who is to blame for this
        disaster? What is your occupation? Where do you come from? What is your country?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CI am a Hebrew, and I [reverently] fear
        and worship the Lord, the God of heaven, who made the sea and the dry land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the men became extremely frightened and said to him, \u201CHow
        could you do this?\u201D For the men knew that he was running from the presence
        of the Lord, because he had told them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then they said to him, \u201CWhat should we do to you, so that the
        sea will become calm for us?\u201D\u2014for the sea was becoming more and
        more violent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Jonah said to them, \u201CPick me up and throw me into the sea. Then
        the sea will become calm for you, for I know that it is because of me that
        this great storm has come upon you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Nevertheless, the men rowed hard [breaking through the waves] to
        return to land, but they could not, because the sea became even more violent
        [surging higher] against them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then they called on the Lord and said, \u201CPlease, O Lord, do not
        let us perish because of taking this man\u2019s life, and do not make us
        accountable for innocent blood; for You, O Lord, have done as You pleased.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So they picked up Jonah and threw him into the sea, and the sea stopped
        its raging. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then the men greatly feared the Lord, and they offered a sacrifice
        to the Lord and made vows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Now the Lord had prepared (appointed, destined) a great fish to swallow
        Jonah. And Jonah was in the stomach of the fish three days and three nights.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jonah\u2019s Prayer"
      title: "Jonah\u2019s Prayer"
      number: 1
      content: '  Then Jonah prayed to the Lord his God from the stomach of the fish, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "and said,\u201CI called out of my trouble and distress to the Lord,And
        He answered me;Out of the belly of Sheol I cried for help,And You heard my
        voice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For You cast me into the deep,Into the [deep] heart of the seas,And
        the currents surrounded and engulfed me;All Your breakers and billowing waves
        passed over me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u2018I have been cast out of Your sight.Nevertheless
        I will look again toward Your holy temple.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The waters surrounded me, to the point of death.The great deep engulfed
        me,Seaweed was wrapped around my head.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I descended to the [very] roots of the mountains.The earth with its
        bars closed behind me [bolting me in] forever,Yet You have brought up my
        life from the pit (death), O Lord my God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When my soul was fainting within me,I remembered the Lord,And my
        prayer came to You,Into Your holy temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Those who regard and follow worthless idols  Turn away from their
        [living source of] mercy and lovingkindness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But [as for me], I will sacrifice to YouWith the voice of thanksgiving;I
        shall pay that which I have vowed.Salvation is from the Lord!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So the Lord commanded the fish, and it vomited Jonah up onto the dry
        land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Nineveh Repents'
      title: Nineveh Repents
      number: 1
      content: '  Now the word of the Lord came to Jonah the second time, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CGo to Nineveh the great city and declare to it the message
        which I am going to tell you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Jonah went to Nineveh in accordance with the word of the Lord.
        Now Nineveh was an exceedingly great city, a three days\u2019 walk [about
        sixty miles in circumference]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then on the first day\u2019s walk, Jonah began to go through the
        city, and he called out and said, \u201CForty days more [remain] and [then]
        Nineveh will be overthrown!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The people of Nineveh believed and trusted in God; and they proclaimed
        a fast and put on sackcloth [in penitent mourning], from the greatest even
        to the least of them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When word reached the king of Nineveh [of Jonah\u2019s message from
        God], he rose from his throne, took off his robe, covered himself with sackcloth
        and sat in the dust [in repentance]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He issued a proclamation and it said, \u201CIn Nineveh, by the decree
        of the king and his nobles: No man, animal, herd, or flock is to taste anything.
        They are not to eat or drink water. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But both man and animal must be covered with sackcloth; and every
        one is to call on God earnestly and forcefully that each may turn from his
        wicked way and from the violence that is in his hands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Who knows, God may turn [in compassion] and relent and withdraw His
        burning anger (judgment) so that we will not perish.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: When God saw their deeds, that they turned from their wicked way,
        then God [had compassion and] relented concerning the disaster which He had
        declared that He would bring upon them. And He did not do it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Jonah\u2019s Displeasure Rebuked"
      title: "Jonah\u2019s Displeasure Rebuked"
      number: 1
      content: '  But it greatly displeased Jonah and he became angry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He prayed to the Lord and said, \u201CO Lord, is this not what I
        said when I was still in my country? That is why I ran to Tarshish, because
        I knew that You are a gracious and compassionate God, slow to anger and great
        in lovingkindness, and [when sinners turn to You] You revoke the [sentence
        of] disaster [against them]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore now, O Lord, just take my life from me, for it is better
        for me to die than to live.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CDo you have a good reason to be angry?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Jonah went out of the city and sat east of it. There he made
        himself a shelter and sat under its shade so that he could see what would
        happen in the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So the Lord God prepared a plant and it grew up over Jonah, to be
        a shade over his head to spare him from discomfort. And Jonah was extremely
        happy about [the protection of] the plant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But God prepared a worm when morning dawned the next day, and it
        attacked the plant and it withered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "When the sun came up God prepared a scorching east wind, and the
        sun beat down on Jonah\u2019s head so that he fainted and he wished to die,
        and said, \u201CIt is better for me to die than to live.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then God said to Jonah, \u201CDo you have a good reason to be angry
        about [the loss of] the plant?\u201D And he said, \u201CI have a [very] good
        reason to be angry, angry enough to die!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the Lord said, \u201CYou had compassion on the plant for which
        you did not work and which you did not cause to grow, which came up overnight
        and perished overnight. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Should I not have compassion on Nineveh, the great city in which
        there are more than 120,000 [innocent] persons, who do not know the difference
        between their right and left hand [and are not yet accountable for sin],
        as well as many [blameless] animals?\u201D"
      comments: []
